kilograms of it to make the reactor core go critical inside <br>
of a steel pressure vessel.<br>
<br>
 You can  also use graphite, or heavy water  as the  moderator in the reactor core.You could encase the uranium rods in the core inside of beryllium sheaths, and you could use the heavy water as the coolant,propellant, and the moderater in the  reactor.<br>
<br>
 These 100% sealed beryllium sheaths make a good neutron reflector, and they ensure that radioactive material can<br>
never be released from the reactor fuel rods.<br>
 <br>
 The natural uranium  reactor can not sustain a nuclear fission reaction without the heavy water, if you use it as the working fluid. The natural uranium can not explode because it is only<br>
.7% U 235  . This kind of atomic reactor with proper shielding<br>
against its nuclear  radiation makes a 100% safe nuclear electric power generator, so long as its core does not get hot enough to break the water into hydrogen and oxygen thus creating a chemical explosion hazard .Using the graphite<br>
core reactor with liquid helium as the coolant for a nuclear electric generator can make a chemical explosion impossible<br>
 if you wish it<br>
<br>
  Also if you take away the heavy water by any means be it accidental or intentional the nuclear fission chain reaction<br>
will stop and the reacter core will shut down naturaly<br>
except for its radioactive decay process. You can use <br>
helium as the propellant and make the reactor explosion<br>
proof.If you use water however the heat could break the water back into hydrogen and oxygen thus creating a chemical explosion hazard.<br>
<br>
Therefore you might use the heavy water system for nuclear<br>
electric generators to power nuclear electric drives,<br>
and you would use the graphite core system with<br>
liquid helium as the coolant, and the propellant for<br>
soliod core nuclear thermal rocket engines. Nuclear engines<br>
with this kind of design can be always 100% safe to operate.<br>
Tim<br>
